# Base image vulnerabilities — cannot fix without upstream python:3.11-slim update.
#
# Sunset policy: every ignore carries a "Re-evaluate" date. When the date
# lands, the entry must be removed and either (a) the upstream patch is
# consumed, (b) the CVE is verifiably not exploitable in our container,
# or (c) a new re-eval date is set with a fresh justification. Accumulating
# forever-ignores is forbidden by this policy.

# ncurses buffer overflow — base image dependency, no user-facing exposure.
# Re-evaluate: 2026-06-01 (next Debian 13 point release window).
CVE-2025-69720

# systemd arbitrary code execution — libsystemd0/libudev1 in the base image;
# we run with no systemd instance so RegisterMachine et al. are unreachable.
# Re-evaluate: 2026-06-01.
CVE-2026-29111

# OpenSSL DoS in Debian 13 — pending 3.5.5-1 patch from Debian security.
# Re-evaluate: 2026-05-15 (Debian typically ships within 4-6 weeks of advisory).
CVE-2026-28390
